The emergence of SARS-CoV-2 follows the general theme of where SARS-CoV and MERS-CoV originated.
While a pancreatic beta-CoV has been identified that shares 95% nucleotide homology with SARS-CoV, there is also a pancreatic CoV that shares 96% nucleotide homology with SARS-CoV-2.
Because civets and other animals on the market have been found to contain viruses similar to SARS-CoV, immediate intermediate hosts for SARS-CoV-2 have not been identified.
