Although questions remain, there is no evidence that SARS-CoV-2 is man-made either intentionally or unintentionally.
CoVs have returned to the limelight due to the recent outbreak of SARS-CoV-2.
Studying CoVs in bats and other animals has rapidly changed our understanding of the importance of zoonotic sources and animal reservoirs of HCoVs in human infection.
Extensive evidence has shown that SARS-CoV, MERS-CoV and SARS-CoV-2 originated in bats and were transmitted to humans via intermediate hosts.
